{
  "texts": [
    "The state vector |𝜓 ⟩ for this system can be expressed as: In this case, each 𝑐 𝑖 𝑗 represents the amplitude corresponding to the basis state |𝑖 𝑗⟩.",
    "The basis states |00⟩, |01⟩, |10⟩, and |11⟩ form a four-state orthonormal basis.",
    "For example, if the system is in the state |𝜓 ⟩ = (1000) 𝑇, it means the amplitude for the state |00⟩ is 1 and 0 for the remaining states |01⟩, |10⟩ and |11⟩.",
    "Consequently, the probability of measuring each state on a computational basis is determined by the squared modulus of their corresponding amplitudes.",
    "In this case |1| 2 = 1 for state |00⟩ and |0| 2 = 0 for the remaining states."
  ]
}